[SN]TITLE[SN]
Pembrokeshire council to discuss Welsh education shake-up

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Welsh education provision in Pembrokeshire is set to be discussed at an extraordinary meeting.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
On Thursday, the council will vote on recommendations to shut Ysgol Gymraeg Glan Cleddau in Haverfordwest and open a school for three to 16-year-olds at Withybush Road.
Post-16 Welsh education would be provided at Ysgol y Preseli.
If approved, a statutory notice will be published on 26 April before a further report is brought to the council.
